'''Neil Yoni El Aynaoui''' ({{langx|ar|نائل العيناوي}}; born 2 July 2001) is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for {{Italian football updater|Roma}} club [[AS Roma|Roma]] and the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

==Club career==

=== Nancy ===
El Aynaoui joined the youth academy of [[AS Nancy Lorraine|Nancy]] when he was 8, and signed his first professional contract with the club on 3 June 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://moroccolatestnews.com/neil-el-aynaoui-signs-his-first-professional-contract-with-as-nancy/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210801185249/https://moroccolatestnews.com/neil-el-aynaoui-signs-his-first-professional-contract-with-as-nancy/|url-status=usurped|archive-date=1 August 2021|title=Neil El Aynaoui signs his first professional contract with AS Nancy|date=3 June 2021}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Nancy in a 4–0 [[Ligue 2]] loss to [[Toulouse FC|Toulouse]] on 31 July 2021.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/07/31/france/ligue-2/association-sportive-nancy-lorraine/toulouse-fc/3525224/|title=Nancy vs. Toulouse - 31 July 2021|website=Soccerway}}</ref>

=== Lens ===
[[File:El Aynaoui rcl asse 2425.png|left|thumb|199x199px|El Aynaoui playing for [[RC Lens|Lens]] in 2023]]
On 29 June 2023, El Aynaoui signed for [[Ligue 1]] club [[RC Lens|Lens]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Mercato : Neil El Aynaoui (Nancy) rejoint Lens |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Neil-el-aynaoui-nancy-rejoint-lens/1405419 |access-date=2023-06-29 |website=L'Équipe |language=fr}}</ref> He scored his first goal on 28 October 2023 against [[FC Nantes]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-11-02 |title=Neil El Aynaoui : "C'est incroyable de marquer pour Lens" |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/neil-el-aynaoui-cest-incroyable-de-marquer-pour-lens-38467781 |access-date=2023-11-02 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref>

=== Roma ===
On 20 July 2025, El Aynaoui moved to [[AS Roma|Roma]] in Italy on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=AS Roma|url=https://www.asroma.com/en/news/73527/neil-el-aynaoui-is-a-roma-player|title=Neil El Aynaoui is a Roma player|date=20 July 2025|access-date=20 July 2025}}</ref> He made his debut for the club against [[Bologna FC 1909|Bologna]] on matchday 1 of the [[Serie A]], by coming off the bench in the 60th minute in place of [[Stephan El Shaarawy|El Shaarawy]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gasperini analyses Bologna win |url=https://www.asroma.com/en/news/73737/gasperini-analyses-bologna-win |access-date=2025-08-27 |website=www.asroma.com |language=en}}</ref>

He scored his first goal for Roma in a [[UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] match against [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] on 27 November 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Roma vs Midtjylland {{!}} UEFA Europa League 2025/26 |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/match/2046227--roma-vs-midtjylland/ |access-date=2026-02-05 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, El Aynaoui holds French and Moroccan nationalities.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.unfp.org/joueur/neil-el-aynaoui-21822/ | title=Neil EL AYNAOUI - }}</ref> He was called up to the [[Morocco national under-23 football team|Morocco U23]]s for a set of friendlies in September 2023.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.lensois.com/neil-el-aynaoui-est-devenu-officiellement-international-marocain-u23/ | title=Neil el Aynaoui est devenu officiellement international marocain U23 | date=8 September 2023 }}</ref>

On 11 December 2025, El Aynaoui was called up to the Morocco squad for the [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations]]. In the final, he iconically got injured in his eye, where they treated him with a bandage and he kept playing to contribute and to participate in the Final.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/afcon2025/news/morocco-name-star-studded-afcon-squad-as-hakimi-makes-cut-but-diop-misses-out/|title=Morocco name star-studded AFCON squad as Hakimi makes cut but Diop misses out|publisher=[[Confederation of African Football]]|date=11 December 2025|access-date=12 December 2025}}</ref>

==Personal life==
El Aynaoui is the son of the retired Moroccan tennis player [[Younes El Aynaoui]].<ref name="Bergaag 2021">{{cite web | title=Neil El Aynaoui signs three years with AS Nancy | website=Bergaag | date=4 June 2021 | url=https://www.bergaag.com/2021/06/04/neil-el-aynaoui-signs-three-years-with-as-nancy.html/ | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210801185250/https://www.bergaag.com/2021/06/04/neil-el-aynaoui-signs-three-years-with-as-nancy.html | url-status=usurped | archive-date=1 August 2021 | access-date=1 August 2021}}</ref>

